CMidi is a C++ class that encapsulates the Linux ALSA 2.0 sound API accessed
by including asoundlib.h and linking to library asound.
c++17 is required for successful compilation.

cmidi.cpp, cmidi.h, and midiloop.cpp, in addition to this file, README,
are (C) Copyright 2026 by Kenneth Witt
These files are licensed under the GPL-2.0 License

An application using CMidi employs the following:
#include "cmidi.h" (which in turn employs "#include <alsa/asoundlib.h>")

